  "text": "The LLVM SelectionDAG type legalization assertion failure 'Cannot expand this type; LLVM lacks the right hooks' traces to the type expansion logic in the SelectionDAG framework. The production build system encounters this when attempting to expand a node type that has no handler.\n\nKey components identified:\n\n1. **Error Source - LegalizeIntegerTypes.cpp (llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/LegalizeIntegerTypes.cpp)**: The ExpandIntegerResult function (starting at line 3024) contains the primary expansion logic for integer types. When encountering an unsupported operation in the switch statement (line 3033), it calls report_fatal_error() at lines 3039-3040 with message 'Do not know how to expand the result of this operator!' This is the main assertion point for integer type expansion failures.\n\n2. **Float Type Expansion - LegalizeFloatTypes.cpp (llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/LegalizeFloatTypes.cpp)**: The ExpandFloatResult function contains similar expansion logic for floating-point types, with the same error handling at lines 1582-1583. Float operand expansion also has error handling at line 2329.\n\n3. **EVT Class Definition - ValueTypes.h (llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/ValueTypes.h)**: The EVT (Extended Value Type) class is defined starting at line 35. The isSimple() method is defined at line 137-139, which checks if a type is a simple value type by verifying that SimpleTy is not INVALID_SIMPLE_VALUE_TYPE. This method is used throughout type legalization to determine if a type requires expansion hooks.\n\n4. **Legalization Orchestration - LegalizeDAG.cpp (llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/LegalizeDAG.cpp)**: The SelectionDAGLegalize class (line 88) orchestrates the overall legalization process with its LegalizeOp method (line 972). This is the entry point for the legalization pass that manages operation legalization.\n\n5. **Type Legalization Framework - LegalizeTypes.h (llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/LegalizeTypes.h)**: The DAGTypeLegalizer class is defined in this header, which manages the overall type legalization process. It coordinates between integer, float, and vector type expansion using functions like ExpandIntegerResult and ExpandFloatResult.\n\nThe error occurs in the type legalization phase when a DAG node with an unsupported type encounters no corresponding expansion handler. The framework checks if types are simple and legal using EVT::isSimple(), and when expansion is required but unavailable, it reports the fatal error. This typically happens when custom hooks for type transformation have not been provided by the target or when the node opcode is not in the expansion switch statements."
}

