his header, which manages the overall type legalization process. It coordinates between integer, float, and vector type expansion using functions like ExpandIntegerResult and ExpandFloatResult.\n\nThe error occurs in the type legalization phase when a DAG node with an unsupported type encounters no corresponding expansion handler. The framework checks if types are simple and legal using EVT::isSimple(), and when expansion is required but unavailable, it reports the fatal error. This typically happens when custom hooks for type transformation have not been provided by the target or when the node opcode is not in the expansion switch statements."
